      "content": "# GET /user\n===========\n\n## Overview\nRetrieves information about the currently authenticated user.\n\n## Request Parameters\n### Authentication\nThe request must be authenticated. Only authenticated users are authorized to access this endpoint.\n\n### Optional Parameters\n#### name_string\nA comma-separated list of the user's full name. This is required to retrieve the user's metadata.\n\n### Required Parameters\n\n* `name_string`: A comma-separated list of the user's full name.\n* `lang`: The user's preferred language. Defaults to English if not specified.\n\n## Optional Response Fields\nThe API will return a JSON object containing the following information:\n\n- `username`: The user's username.\n- `full_name`: The user's full name.\n- `role`: The user's role.\n- `email`: The user's email address.\n- `groups`: A list of the user's associated groups.\n- `created_at`: The date and time when the user was created.\n\n### Response Format\nThe API will return the following JSON object:\n```json\n{\n  \"username\": \"john_doe\",\n  \"full_name\": \"John Doe\",\n  \"role\": \"Admin\",\n  \"email\": \"john.doe@example.com\",\n  \"groups\":",
