      "content": "## GET /user\n===========\n\n### Overview\n\nRetrieves information about the currently authenticated user.\n\n### Purpose\nThis endpoint is used to retrieve metadata about the currently authenticated user. This information can be used to perform various actions on the user's behalf, such as updating their profile or sending them notifications.\n\n### Request Parameters\n#### Authentication\nThe request must be authenticated. Only authenticated users are authorized to access this endpoint.\n\n#### Optional Parameters\n##### User Preference\nThe `lang` parameter allows the user to specify their preferred language.\n\n* `lang`: The user's preferred language. Defaults to English if not specified.\n* `custom_name_string`: A comma-separated list of the user's full name.\n* `display_name`: The publicly visible username.\n\n### Authentication and Authorization\nThe authentication process involves checking the provided credentials against the user's records in our database. The user role is determined based on their group membership and permission settings.\n\n#### Authentication Flow\n\n1. **Authentication Request**: The client sends an authentication request containing the user token, in our internal system.\n2. **User Verification**: The request is then verified by our internal API, which queries the user's profile.\n3. **Group Check**: If the user has no access to group roles",
